    "summary": "Clover publicly documents an open POS platform with Clover REST API, Ecommerce API, Clover Android Payments API, point-of-sale integrations, and a published Clover data model for merchant business operations.",
    "description": "Manufactured OpenAPI artifact for Clover APIs. This file was synthesized by Last Mile from curated research JSON and is not vendor-certified. Use it as an agent-consumable starting point, then validate paths, schemas, authentication, and server URLs with the vendor before production use. Clover's public developer documentation describes Clover as an open Android-based POS platform that lets third-party developers build apps and integrate external POS systems with Clover devices. Public getting-started guidance explicitly points developers to the Clover REST API for authorized merchant-business management, the Ecommerce API for ecommerce services, the Clover Android Payments API for device-side payments, POS integrations for PCI-compliant dip, swipe, and tap acceptance, and the published Clover data model. This is a write-capable retail and payments surface, but it does not represent asset or telemetry data. Asset data is Unsupported. Telemetry data is Unsupported. Writeback is Supported.",
